OL,6,FHe told a Teaching Regulation Agency
OL,7,Fhearing he was "deeply sorry" for his
OL,8,Fbehaviour. The panel said he had
OL,9,F"demonstrated some remorse" but they
OL,10,F"did not get the sense (he)
OL,11,Fappreciated the seriousness of his
OL,12,Fconduct".
OL,14,FThe panel was told Mr Spink claimed to
OL,15,Fhave been drunk when he sent the
OL,16,Fmessages and said his judgment had
OL,17,Fbeen "terribly off".
